Articles.Content:
I'm assuming you've all seen this artwork. I'm curious as to the mods used. (KAS, Interstellar, etc...) Specifically I'm interested in the spherical tanks used.

<iframe width="480" height="270" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/LzH1ZEmkbAI?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="true"></iframe>

If it's been addressed I haven't found the thread. And yes, I googled the .... out of it before coming here. This is my last resort.

Spherical tanks are parts from zzz that are just basically empty models, but are in public domain to be used and appropiated in a mod: [http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/43840-Hab-Hub-%28and-other-strange-things%29](https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/43840-Hab-Hub-%28and-other-strange-things%29)

Since the video uploader and zzz share the same avatar (and the zzz in the name), I assume they are the same person, and other strange looking parts are also custom-made.

Edit:

I will try to identify anything I can though, will update as I find them.

Radiator from the same person, with the box from old KAS, but model from the same person. Not sure on the engine and that nuclear reactor, but might be from them, has the same style.

Noticed some B9 parts in there (all the space planes are from B9 parts, a B9 body on the big ship, along with air brakes and RCS)

Some hex truss: [http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/86388-1-0-Speedy-s-Hex-Truss-System](https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/86388-1-0-Speedy-s-Hex-Truss-System)

RPM screen for IVA

There is a SCANSAT radar in there, but undeployed.

Hmm, the fuelcell might be custom too, I thought it was modular rocket, but that is different.

Not recognizing the cylinders next to the KAS boxes. Nor the top of the small ship at the end...I guess I can't find anymore. Good luck.

**Edited <time datetime="2015-06-22T16:45:41Z" title="06/22/2015 04:45  PM" data-short="9 yr">June 22, 2015</time> by RainDreamer**

Fantastic, thank you. I presumed the reactor was Interstellar. It looks the same anyways.

Thanks again.
zzz does design quite a few parts for interstellar, so I guess there are similarities.
